for behaviors that occur frequently, there will be little difference between the means reported by each half of the class. For example, the two halves of the class should be quite similar on mean number of tail shakes, simply because this occurs almost continuously among geese. Horlvever, for relatively infrequent behaviors, such as displays of agglession, students are likely to notice differences between
